<p>In your code, you’re essentially telling your pose estimation to never use the angle from the limelight poses and always use your gyro. This is totally valid approach, but points to the issue being in your gyro’s value relative to the field coordinate system and pose estimator.</p>
<p>You’ll want to make sure that when you reset your odometry, your initial heading gets set correctly. We had really good luck by just running an auto to initialize our heading to a known starting heading.</p>
<p>Also be sure to reset your post estimator’s odometry at the start of auto inside in the “resetOdometry” method. Right now you’re only resetting your wheel/gyro estimation.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-04-25T22:49:21.872Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":88,"readers_count":87,"score":72.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":464553,"topic_slug":"swerve-drive-heading-offset-with-pose-estimator","display_username":"Sam Viesselman","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":37087,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/swerve-drive-heading-offset-with-pose-estimator/464553/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3374426,"name":null,"username":"5348-Programmer","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/5348-programmer/{size}/216874_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-26T14:14:53.246Z","cooked":"<p>I added this line of code in the resetOdometry method, and it seemed to fix the problem.</p>
